line and Mercs falling into the Blademaster line.  <br>
<br>
  Now, that being the case, what exactly should a 'Light Tank' Be like?  I'm asking everyone on several forums this because I'm trying to get an idea if what everyone wants is just yet another gimp class, kind of like I expect.  While answering, try to be specific and cover all the bases.  Define just how much defensive capability they should have, how much offensive power and really what you expect what kind of role they should take in the game.<br>
<br>
  Sentack <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#000000>(4/9/03 2:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question: What do you think a 'Light Tank' should be lik</span><hr size=1> A Light Tank should be a &quot;fast&quot; class that can kill quickly if left alone.  How fast depends on the survivability.  So a Berserker who has nothing but offense and Studded should be the best at it (within reason), followed by the Blademaster who also has studded but can take out a shield/bow for more &quot;utility&quot; and Mercenaries should come last (at killing quickly among the light tanks) since he/she gets Chain Armor.<br>
<br>
When 2 groups both containing casters and light tanks come face to face, there needs to be a tactical decision:<br>
<br>
1) Take out the big hitters (casters) who can do awesome damage very fast from range or other support classes which increase survivability of a group.<br>
<br>
2) Take out the other light tanks who are trying to take out your survivability or your big hitters.<br>
<br>
All Light Tanks should kill fast (compared to a non-light tank...this doesn't mean 2 shotting an opponent), but the flip side is if the Light Tank gets too much attention, he/she goes down just as fast as he/she can take down any opponent. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#000000>(4/27/03 8:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question: What do you think a 'Light Tank' should be lik</span><hr size=1> A Light Tank should draw even in a duel with a polearmsman, assuming they are both using suitable weapon types, eg both Slash in the case of Albion Chain and ALbion plate both being neutral to this weapon type.<br>
