<br>
Our damage over time should be more effective but the fact tat we have mroe DoT shouldn't detract from the fact that our job is to kill a target QUICKER than an armsman/hero/warrior, whether he's offensive (2H, pole, LW) or defensive (Sword and Board) <br>
<br>
What this means is that though the polearm/2H can deal tremendous up-front offense we should be able to catch up and overtake this scaling very qquickly.<br>
<br>
IMHO that means that starting at the word go with a front-loading polearm as a contender, a CDWLA tank should have caught up the polearmsmans DoT by the 2nd/3rd hit and overtaken by the 4th.<br>
<br>
This still means that we've gotta wait 9-12 seconds before we can start going &quot;ha! superior damage&quot; but anything over this is overpowerment.<br>
<br>
It's generally a defensive heavy tanks job to protect casters with their slam. An offensive heavy tank (2H) should be a decent caster-killer like the light tank, but as above should be &quot;penalised&quot; in performance through his slowness.<br>
<br>
And most importantly, any fast attack speed shouldn't be a penalty to our damage. IN CDW fast atttack speeds are required as we don't DW all the time. IN LA people have exploited the &quot;you get mroe damage per hit if your delay is slower&quot; by even going to the extent of duelling casters so as to have their quickness debuffed meaning mroe front-loading damage. Slow speed should be a ponderous, ticking, nightmarish curse that makes people want to cry, not a bullet-time slow-motion effect before the target falls dead in 1-2 hits.<br>
<br>
Likewise, the light tank (ALL LIGHT TANKS) should relish the high speed of his attacks, and be more like &quot;Fist of the North Star&quot; Kenshiro than Scrappy-Doo.<br>
<br>
Remember, we're good at making our weak opponents suddenly cut-down. So we should his fast, to bust PBT, crit, DW, PF and proc Dots, DDs and DTs a lot.<br>
