<br>
Yes, the attack hinderance ability of the heavy tank won't completely stop a light tank from killing off a caster. It is not meant to. Remember though, that the ability will also allow the attacked caster to continue casting spells to heal himself or nuke/stun the light tank. The heavy tank isn't totally protecting the caster, but helping him to defend himself. If I were a nuker, I would much rather have the proposed heavy tank defending me because I could then get off a spell and kill my attacker. However, a light tank defending me would not help me cast any spells, and I would probably be dead before the enemy was killed off by the tank.<br>
<br>
Front end damage superiority of polearm users is most significant because RvR damage is so high and people die so fast. I find the fast kill rate annoying anyway, and I think others do too. If combat were simply slowed down and everybody did less damage, the front end damage would be less of a problem because light tanks would do more damage over time.<br>
<br>
Another thing that would help all fast weapon users would be to change the weapon speed delay system so that the delay occurs BEFORE the first weapon strike. That way, when a fast weapon user and a slow weapon user press the attack button at the same time, the fast weapon user hits first. Let's say that a fast weapon does half the damage of a slow one, but attacks at double the rate. When both attacks first attack, the fast weapon will hit once for half the damage of the slow one. Then, the fast weapon will hit again at the same time as the slow weapon's first strike. The fast weapon again, does half the damage of the slow weapon. By this time, the fast weapon has two half damage strikes, and the slow weapon has one full damage strike, and the damage is identical. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 313<br> <font color=#000000>(5/10/03 3:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> how to make US mroe &quot;offensive&quot; than 2H frontload</span><hr size=1> That's actually a very good theory, IMHO.<br>
