<br>
An interesting change to flurry might be to take it off its current timer, and put it on a short after-combat-readying timer, similar to assassin venoms. It would work as follows:<br>
<br>
While you aren't attacking, and nobody is beating on you, you activate flurry with a hot button. On your next melee attack, your opponent is hit by the flurry in addition to your normal damage. You finish the fight as normal. Afterwards, you wait a moment for the combat timer to run, and then you again prepare (apply) the flurry to be used on your next attack.<br>
<br>
The above change would keep flurry as a front end damage bonus, as it was orignally meant to be. The removal of the timer between uses would allow flurry to be used more often. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 360<br> <font color=#000000>(5/21/03 4:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question: What do you think a 'Light Tank' should be lik</span><hr size=1> That would be very cool, like a self-applying poison insta-DD thing.<br>
